<subSubSection id="7DAA6500B83ABF589BE17FB3967EFCB9" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="446" pageId="1" pageNumber="444" type="description">
<paragraph id="350F368BB83ABF5A9BE17FB3911DF839" blockId="1.[151,1437,1339,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">
<emphasis id="07C4EA99B83ABF5A9BE17FB3942FF911" bold="true" box="[199,345,1699,1725]" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Description.</emphasis>
Body length without antennae 2.3–3.0 mm. Colour in alcohol bluish-grey, ocular plate bluishblack. Tegumental granulation strong. Antennae as long as head. Ant. I with 7 chaetae, Ant. II with 11 chaetae and Ant. III with 18 ordinary chaetae. Ant. III and IV fused dorsally, ventral separation well marked. Sensory organ of Ant. III consisting of two small, globular internal sensilla, two subcylindrical guard sensilla (ventral sensillum as long as dorsal one) and two guard chaetae between them; ventral microsensillum present. Ant. IV with about 35 ordinary chaetae, 8-9 short and truncate chaetae in ventro-apical part and 6 distinct subcylindrical sensilla; dorsoexternal microsensillum and subapical organite present; apical vesicle trilobed (
<figureCitation id="AD8B2A0EB83ABF5A98DE7E6B9128F839" box="[1016,1118,1915,1941]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,192,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[152,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Pseudachorutes hyrcanicus sp. nov. 1, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 2, central area of head between d3 and d5 chaetae; 3, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 4, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 5a, chaetotaxy of labrum; 5b, labial chaetotaxy; 6, PAO and eyes; 7, distal part of leg III; 8, mandible; 9, maxilla; 10, furca; 11, chaetotaxy of Abds. II–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623159/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="350F368BB83ABF589BE17E8F9715FF55" blockId="1.[151,1437,1339,2014]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,150,1077]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="446" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">
PAO slightly elongated with 15–19 vesicles, as long as 1.5 ocellus B (
<figureCitation id="AD8B2A0EB83ABF5A98F07E8F916CF816" box="[982,1050,1951,1978]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,192,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[152,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Pseudachorutes hyrcanicus sp. nov. 1, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 2, central area of head between d3 and d5 chaetae; 3, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 4, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 5a, chaetotaxy of labrum; 5b, labial chaetotaxy; 6, PAO and eyes; 7, distal part of leg III; 8, mandible; 9, maxilla; 10, furca; 11, chaetotaxy of Abds. II–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623159/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). 8+8 eyes. Buccal cone relatively short as 1.4 Ant. I lengths. Mandibles fork-like with four teeth, styliform maxilla with two lamellae, one of them with tiny apical hook (
<figureCitation id="AD8B2A0EB838BF589AA979879484FF1D" box="[399,498,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,192,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[152,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Pseudachorutes hyrcanicus sp. nov. 1, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 2, central area of head between d3 and d5 chaetae; 3, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 4, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 5a, chaetotaxy of labrum; 5b, labial chaetotaxy; 6, PAO and eyes; 7, distal part of leg III; 8, mandible; 9, maxilla; 10, furca; 11, chaetotaxy of Abds. II–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Figs 8, 9</figureCitation>
). Labral formula: 4/2,3,4 (
<figureCitation id="AD8B2A0EB838BF5898317987961EFF1D" box="[791,872,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,192,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[152,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Pseudachorutes hyrcanicus sp. nov. 1, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 2, central area of head between d3 and d5 chaetae; 3, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 4, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 5a, chaetotaxy of labrum; 5b, labial chaetotaxy; 6, PAO and eyes; 7, distal part of leg III; 8, mandible; 9, maxilla; 10, furca; 11, chaetotaxy of Abds. II–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Fig. 5a</figureCitation>
). Labium without organites x and papillate chaetae L, with 11+11 ordinary chaetae (
<figureCitation id="AD8B2A0EB838BF58992279AB9721FF79" box="[516,599,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,192,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[152,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Pseudachorutes hyrcanicus sp. nov. 1, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 2, central area of head between d3 and d5 chaetae; 3, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 4, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 5a, chaetotaxy of labrum; 5b, labial chaetotaxy; 6, PAO and eyes; 7, distal part of leg III; 8, mandible; 9, maxilla; 10, furca; 11, chaetotaxy of Abds. II–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Fig. 5b</figureCitation>
). Perilabial area with 4+4 subequal chaetae. The central granulated area on head between 
<emphasis id="07C4EA99B838BF589A1179CF9433FF55" box="[311,325,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">d</emphasis>
3– 
<emphasis id="07C4EA99B838BF589A4779CF9419FF55" box="[353,367,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">d</emphasis>
5 chaetae as in 
<figureCitation id="AD8B2A0EB838BF58993C79CF9729FF55" box="[538,607,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,192,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[152,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Pseudachorutes hyrcanicus sp. nov. 1, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 2, central area of head between d3 and d5 chaetae; 3, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 4, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 5a, chaetotaxy of labrum; 5b, labial chaetotaxy; 6, PAO and eyes; 7, distal part of leg III; 8, mandible; 9, maxilla; 10, furca; 11, chaetotaxy of Abds. II–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
