<emphasis id="07C4EA99B838BF58990C78A7974EFE7C" box="[554,568,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">p</emphasis>
3 and 
<emphasis id="07C4EA99B838BF58995B78A797FDFE7C" box="[637,651,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">p</emphasis>
4 chaetae present), S-chaeta = 
<emphasis id="07C4EA99B838BF5898C778A79699FE7C" box="[993,1007,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">p</emphasis>
3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="350F368BB838BF589BE178CB9698FDB5" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,1077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">
Ventral chaetotaxy on Abds. II–VI as in 
<figureCitation id="AD8B2A0EB838BF5899AE78CB97AFFE59" box="[648,729,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,192,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[152,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Pseudachorutes hyrcanicus sp. nov. 1, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 2, central area of head between d3 and d5 chaetae; 3, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 4, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 5a, chaetotaxy of labrum; 5b, labial chaetotaxy; 6, PAO and eyes; 7, distal part of leg III; 8, mandible; 9, maxilla; 10, furca; 11, chaetotaxy of Abds. II–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
. Thoracic sterna without chaetae, VT with 3+3 chaetae. Abds. I without chaetae, Abds. II with 4+4 chaetae, Abds. III with 7–8+7–8 chaetae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="350F368BB838BF589BE17B339035FDCD" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,1077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">
Dens with six chaetae (
<figureCitation id="AD8B2A0EB838BF589AF47B339751FD91" box="[466,551,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,192,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[152,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Pseudachorutes hyrcanicus sp. nov. 1, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 2, central area of head between d3 and d5 chaetae; 3, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 4, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 5a, chaetotaxy of labrum; 5b, labial chaetotaxy; 6, PAO and eyes; 7, distal part of leg III; 8, mandible; 9, maxilla; 10, furca; 11, chaetotaxy of Abds. II–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Mucro boat-shaped, with curved ventral edge and one broad lateral lamella. Manubrium with 12+12 chaetae. Tenaculum with 3+3 teeth. Each anal valve with two chaetae 
<emphasis id="07C4EA99B838BF589F9D7B5791A2FDCD" box="[1211,1236,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">hr</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="AD8B2A0EB838BF589FC57B579043FDCD" box="[1251,1333,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,192,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[152,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Pseudachorutes hyrcanicus sp. nov. 1, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 2, central area of head between d3 and d5 chaetae; 3, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 4, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 5a, chaetotaxy of labrum; 5b, labial chaetotaxy; 6, PAO and eyes; 7, distal part of leg III; 8, mandible; 9, maxilla; 10, furca; 11, chaetotaxy of Abds. II–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="350F368BB838BF589BE17B7B967EFCB9" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,1077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">
Tibiotarsi of legs I, II and III with 18, 18 and 17 chaetae, respectively, chaetae M and B7 absent on tibiotarsus III (
<figureCitation id="AD8B2A0EB838BF589BE57B9F947EFD05" box="[195,264,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,192,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[152,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Pseudachorutes hyrcanicus sp. nov. 1, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 2, central area of head between d3 and d5 chaetae; 3, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 4, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 5a, chaetotaxy of labrum; 5b, labial chaetotaxy; 6, PAO and eyes; 7, distal part of leg III; 8, mandible; 9, maxilla; 10, furca; 11, chaetotaxy of Abds. II–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Femora I, II and III with 13, 12 and 11 chaetae, trochanters I, II and III with 6, 6 and 6 chaetae, coxae I, II and III with 3, 6 and 7 chaetae, subcoxae 2 of legs I, II and III with 0, 2 and 2 chaetae, subcoxae 1 of legs I, II and III with 1, 2 and 2 chaetae, respectively. Claw with a strong tooth near middle of inner edge and without lateral teeth in basal part (
<figureCitation id="AD8B2A0EB838BF589A4B7BEB94C7FCB9" box="[365,433,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,192,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[152,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Pseudachorutes hyrcanicus sp. nov. 1, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 2, central area of head between d3 and d5 chaetae; 3, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 4, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 5a, chaetotaxy of labrum; 5b, labial chaetotaxy; 6, PAO and eyes; 7, distal part of leg III; 8, mandible; 9, maxilla; 10, furca; 11, chaetotaxy of Abds. II–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Empodial appendage absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7DAA6500B838BF589BE17A0F94F5FCF1" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="350F368BB838BF589BE17A0F94F5FCF1" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,1077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis id="07C4EA99B838BF589BE17A0F9438FC95" bold="true" box="[199,334,799,825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the new species refers to the Hyrcanian forest (
<collectingCountry id="4DA7761BB838BF5898D57A0F9153FC95" box="[1011,1061,799,825]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Iran</collectingCountry>
), the region where the 
<typeStatus id="EA0B8829B838BF589E057A0F9025FC95" box="[1315,1363,799,825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">type</typeStatus>
specimens were collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7DAA6500B838BF589BE17A769074FB99" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="350F368BB838BF589BE17A769074FB99" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,1077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis id="07C4EA99B838BF589BE17A76943AFC2C" bold="true" box="[199,332,870,896]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Discussion.</emphasis>
The new species is related to 
<taxonomicName id="F2B04D08B838BF5899BD7A77911DFC2D" authority="Krausbauer, 1898" authorityName="Krausbauer" authorityYear="1898" box="[667,1131,871,897]" class="Collembola" family="Neanuridae" genus="Pseudachorutes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubius">
<emphasis id="07C4EA99B838BF5899BD7A7796E9FC2D" box="[667,927,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Pseudachorutes dubius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="51214B7AB838BF5898807A77911DFC2D" author="Krausbauer, Th." box="[934,1131,871,897]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" pagination="501 - 504" refId="ref5480" refString="Krausbauer, Th. (1898) Neue Collembola aus der Umgebung von Weilburg a. / Lahn. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 21 (568), 501 - 504." type="journal article" year="1898">Krausbauer, 1898</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F2B04D08B838BF589F877A7790EAFC2D" authorityName="Kaprus, IJ &amp; Weiner, WM" authorityYear="2009" box="[1185,1436,871,897]" class="Collembola" family="Neanuridae" genus="Pseudachorutes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitalii">
<emphasis id="07C4EA99B838BF589F877A7790EAFC2D" box="[1185,1436,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Pseudachorutes vitalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kaprus’ &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="51214B7AB838BF589A347A9B94DCFC09" author="Weiner, W." box="[274,426,907,933]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref5423" refString="Kaprus', I. J. &amp; Weiner, W. (2009) The genus Pseudachorutes Tullberg, 1871 (Collembola, Neanuridae) in the Ukraine with descriptions of new species. Zootaxa, 2166 (1), 1 - 23. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2166.1.1" type="journal article" year="2009">Weiner, 2009</bibRefCitation>
. These three species have the same 
<typeStatus id="EA0B8829B838BF5898117A9B9611FC09" box="[823,871,907,933]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">type</typeStatus>
of chaetotaxy on head (present unpaired chaeta 
<emphasis id="07C4EA99B838BF589EA67A9B90F8FC09" box="[1408,1422,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">d</emphasis>
1 and absent 
<emphasis id="07C4EA99B838BF589A357ABF9457FC64" box="[275,289,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">a</emphasis>
0 chaeta), labral formula of chaetae (4/2,3,4), shape of apical bulb (trilobed), shape of mucro (with long and broad lateral lamella) and number of chaetae on Tht. II and III (10+10 chaetae each, 
<emphasis id="07C4EA99B838BF589F487AC3910AFC40" box="[1134,1148,979,1004]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">a</emphasis>
2 chaeta absent), VT (3+3 chaetae), tibiotarsi of legs I-III (18, 18, 17 each) and on dens (6 chaetae). These species differ distinctly in number of chaetae on Tht. I, details of chaetotaxy Abdt. I–V, number of teeth at mandible and claw (Table 1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
